421.description: It is docile as a bud, but turns cheerful when it blooms. It folds back into a bud if sunlight wanes.

422.name: Shellos
422.description: Its colors and shapes differ from region to region. In the Sinnoh region, two types are confirmed.

423.name: Gastrodon
423.description: It has a pliable body without any bones. If any part of its body is torn off, it grows right back.

424.name: Ambipom
424.description: They work in large colonies and make rings by linking their tails, apparently in friendship.

425.name: Drifloon
425.description: It tugs on the hands of children to steal them away. However, it gets pulled around instead.

426.name: Drifblim
426.description: It’s drowzy in daytime, but flies off in the evening in big groups. No one knows where they go.

427.name: Buneary
427.description: When it senses danger, it perks up its ears. On cold nights, it sleeps with its head tucked into its fur.

428.name: Lopunny
428.description: An extremely cautious Pokémon. It cloaks its body with its fluffy ear fur when it senses danger.

428.name: Mega Lopunny
428.description: An extremely cautious Pokémon. It cloaks its body with its fluffy ear fur when it senses danger.

429.name: Mismagius
429.description: Its cries sound like incantations. Those hearing it are tormented by headaches and hallucinations.

430.name: Honchkrow
430.description: It makes its MURKROW cronies bring it food. It idles its time away, grooming itself in its nest.

431.name: Glameow
431.description: It claws if displeased and purrs when affectionate. Its fickleness is very popular among some.

432.name: Purugly
432.description: It is a brazen brute that barges its way into another Pokémon’s nest and claims it as its own.

433.name: Chingling
433.description: Each time it hops, it makes a ringing sound. It deafens foes by emitting high-frequency cries.

434.name: Stunky
434.description: It protects itself by spraying a noxious fluid from its rear. The stench lingers for 24 hours.

435.name: Skuntank
435.description: It sprays a stinky fluid from its tail. The fluid smells worse the longer it is allowed to fester.

436.name: Bronzor
436.description: Implements shaped like it were discovered in ancient tombs. It is unknown if they are related.

437.name: Bronzong
437.description: One caused a news sensation when it was dug up at a construction site after a 2,000-year sleep.

438.name: Bonsly
438.description: It looks as if it is always crying. It is actually adjusting its body’s fluid levels by eliminating excess.

439.name: Mime Jr.
439.description: It likes places where people gather. It mimics foes to confuse them, then makes its getaway.

440.name: Happiny
440.description: It loves round white things. It carries an egg-shaped rock in imitation of CHANSEY.

441.name: Chatot
441.description: It can learn and speak human words. If they gather, they all learn the same saying.

442.name: Spiritomb
442.description: It was bound to a fissure in an odd keystone as punishment for misdeeds 500 years ago.

443.name: Gible
443.description: It nests in small, horizontal holes in cave walls. It pounces to catch prey that stray too close.

444.name: Gabite
444.description: There is a long-held belief that medicine made from its scales will heal even incurable illnesses.

445.name: Garchomp
445.description: When it folds up its body and extends its wings, it looks like a jet plane. It flies at sonic speed.

445.name: Mega Garchomp
445.description: When it folds up its body and extends its wings, it looks like a jet plane. It flies at sonic speed.

446.name: Munchlax
446.description: It wolfs down its weight in food once a day, swallowing food whole with almost no chewing.

447.name: Riolu
447.description: Its body is lithe yet powerful. It can crest three mountains and cross two canyons in one night.

448.name: Lucario
448.description: By catching the aura emanating from others, it can read their thoughts and movements.

448.name: Mega Lucario
448.description: By catching the aura emanating from others, it can read their thoughts and movements.

449.name: Hippopotas
449.description: It enshrouds itself with sand to protect itself from germs. It does not enjoy getting wet.

450.name: Hippowdon
450.description: It blasts internally stored sand from ports on its body to create a towering twister for attack.

451.name: Skorupi
451.description: It grips prey with its tail claws and injects poison. It tenaciously hangs on until the poison takes.

452.name: Drapion
452.description: It has the power in its clawed arms to make scrap of a car. The tips of its claws release poison.

453.name: Croagunk
453.description: Its cheeks hold poison sacs. It tries to catch foes off guard to jab them with toxic fingers.

454.name: Toxicroak
454.description: The toxin made in its poison sacs is pumped to the knuckle claws through tubes down its arms.

455.name: Carnivine
455.description: It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling saliva, then chomps down. It takes a whole day to eat prey.

456.name: Finneon
456.description: After long exposure to sunlight, the patterns on its tail fins shine vividly when darkness arrives.

457.name: Lumineon
457.description: To avoid detection by predators, it crawls along the seafloor using the two fins on its chest.

458.name: Mantyke
458.description: A friendly Pokémon that captures the subtle flows of seawater using its two antennae.

459.name: Snover
459.description: It lives on snowy mountains. Having had little contact with humans, it is boldly inquisitive.

460.name: Abomasnow
460.description: It whips up blizzards in mountains that are always buried in snow. It is the abominable snowman.

460.name: Mega Abomasnow
460.description: It whips up blizzards in mountains that are always buried in snow. It is the abominable snowman.

461.name: Weavile
461.description: They live in cold regions, forming groups of four or five that hunt prey with impressive coordination.

462.name: Magnezone
462.description: A group tried to use scientific means to make MAGNEZONE evolve, but their efforts ended in failure.

463.name: Lickilicky
463.description: It wraps things with its extensible tongue. Getting too close to it will leave you soaked with drool.

464.name: Rhyperior
464.description: It puts rocks in holes in its palms and uses its muscles to shoot them. GEODUDE are shot at rare times.

465.name: Tangrowth
465.description: Its arms are made of plants that bind themselves to things. They grow back right away if cut.

466.name: Electivire
466.description: It pushes the tips of its two tails against the foe, then lets loose with over 20,000 volts of power.

467.name: Magmortar
467.description: It blasts fireballs of over 3,600 degrees F from the ends of its arms. It lives in volcanic craters.

468.name: Togekiss
468.description: It shares many blessings with people who respect one another’s rights and avoid needless strife.

469.name: Yanmega
469.description: By churning its wings, it creates shock waves that inflict critical internal injuries to foes.

470.name: Leafeon
470.description: It basically does not fight. With cells similar to those of plants, it can perform photosynthesis.

471.name: Glaceon
471.description: As a protective technique, it can completely freeze its fur to make its hairs stand like needles.

472.name: Gliscor
472.description: It observes prey while hanging inverted from branches. When the chance presents itself, it swoops!

473.name: Mamoswine
473.description: Its impressive tusks are made of ice. The population thinned when it turned warm after the ice age.

474.name: Porygon-Z
474.description: Additional software was installed to make it a better Pokémon. It began acting oddly, however.

475.name: Gallade
475.description: When trying to protect someone, it extends its elbows as if they were swords and fights savagely.

475.name: Mega Gallade
475.description: When trying to protect someone, it extends its elbows as if they were swords and fights savagely.

476.name: Probopass
476.description: It exudes strong magnetism from all over. It controls three small units called Mini-Noses.

477.name: Dusknoir
477.description: The antenna on its head captures radio waves from the world of spirits that command it to take people there.

478.name: Froslass
478.description: It freezes foes with an icy breath nearly -60 degrees F. What seems to be its body is actually hollow.

479.name: Rotom
479.description: Its body is composed of plasma. It is known to infiltrate electronic devices and wreak havoc.

479.name: Heat Rotom
479.description: Its body is composed of plasma. It is known to infiltrate electronic devices and wreak havoc.

479.name: Wash Rotom
479.description: Its body is composed of plasma. It is known to infiltrate electronic devices and wreak havoc.

479.name: Frost Rotom
479.description: Its body is composed of plasma. It is known to infiltrate electronic devices and wreak havoc.

479.name: Fan Rotom
479.description: Its body is composed of plasma. It is known to infiltrate electronic devices and wreak havoc.

479.name: Mow Rotom
479.description: Its body is composed of plasma. It is known to infiltrate electronic devices and wreak havoc.

480.name: Uxie
480.description: Known as “The Being of Knowledge.” It is said that it can wipe out the memory of those who see its eyes.

481.name: Mesprit
481.description: Known as “The Being of Emotion.” It taught humans the nobility of sorrow, pain, and joy.

482.name: Azelf
482.description: Known as “The Being of Willpower.” It sleeps at the bottom of a lake to keep the world in balance.

483.name: Dialga
483.description: A Pokémon spoken of in legend. It is said that time began moving when DIALGA was born.

484.name: Palkia
484.description: It is said to live in a gap in the spatial dimension parallel to ours. It appears in mythology.

485.name: Heatran
485.description: It dwells in volcanic caves. It digs in with its cross-shaped feet to crawl on ceilings and walls.

486.name: Regigigas
486.description: It is said to have made Pokémon that look like itself from a special ice mountain, rocks, and magma.

487.name: Giratina - Altered Forme
487.description: A Pokémon that is said to live in a world on the reverse side of ours. It appears in an ancient cemetery.

487.name: Giratina - Origin Forme
487.description: A Pokémon that is said to live in a world on the reverse side of ours. It appears in an ancient cemetery.

488.name: Cresselia
488.description: Shiny particles are released from its wings like a veil. It is said to represent the crescent moon.

489.name: Phione
489.description: A Pokémon that lives in warm seas. It inflates the flotation sac on its head to drift and search for food.

490.name: Manaphy
490.description: Born on a cold seafloor, it will swim great distances to return to its birthplace.

491.name: Darkrai
491.description: Folklore has it that on moonless nights, this Pokémon will make people see horrific nightmares.

492.name: Shaymin - Land Forme
492.description: It lives in flower patches and avoids detection by curling up to look like a flowering plant.

492.name: Shaymin - Sky Forme
492.description: It lives in flower patches and avoids detection by curling up to look like a flowering plant.

493.name: Arceus
493.description: It is described in mythology as the Pokémon that shaped the universe with its 1,000 arms.

494.name: Victini
494.description: This Pokémon brings victory. It is said that Trainers with Victini always win, regardless of the type of encounter.

495.name: Snivy
495.description: They photosynthesize by bathing their tails in sunlight. When they are not feeling well, their tails droop.

496.name: Servine
496.description: They avoid attacks by sinking into the shadows of thick foliage. They retaliate with masterful whipping techniques.

497.name: Serperior
497.description: They raise their heads to intimidate opponents but only give it their all when fighting a powerful opponent.

498.name: Tepig
498.description: It can deftly dodge its foe’s attacks while shooting fireballs from its nose. It roasts berries before it eats them.

499.name: Pignite
499.description: Whatever it eats becomes fuel for the flame in its stomach. When it is angered, the intensity of the flame increases.

500.name: Emboar
500.description: It can throw a fire punch by setting its fists on fire with its fiery chin. It cares deeply about its friends.

501.name: Oshawott
501.description: The scalchop on its stomach is made from the same elements as claws. It detaches the scalchop for use as a blade.

502.name: Dewott
502.description: Scalchop techniques differ from one Dewott to another. It never neglects maintaining its scalchops.

503.name: Samurott
503.description: One swing of the sword incorporated in its armor can fell an opponent. A simple glare from one of them quiets everybody.

504.name: Patrat
504.description: Extremely cautious, they take shifts to maintain a constant watch of their nest. They feel insecure without a lookout.

505.name: Watchog
505.description: They make the patterns on their bodies shine in order to threaten predators. Keen eyesight lets them see in the dark.

506.name: Lillipup
506.description: It faces strong opponents with great courage. But, when at a disadvantage in a fight, this intelligent Pokémon flees.

507.name: Herdier
507.description: It has black, cape-like fur that is very hard and decreases the amount of damage it receives.

508.name: Stoutland
508.description: It rescues people stranded by blizzards in the mountains. Its shaggy fur shields it from the cold.

509.name: Purrloin
509.description: They steal from people for fun, but their victims can’t help but forgive them. Their deceptively cute act is perfect.

510.name: Liepard
510.description: These Pokémon vanish and appear unexpectedly. Many Trainers are drawn to their beautiful form and fur.

511.name: Pansage
511.description: This Pokémon dwells deep in the forest. Eating a leaf from its head whisks weariness away as if by magic.

512.name: Simisage
512.description: Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.

513.name: Pansear
513.description: When it is angered, the temperature of its head tuft reaches 600° F. It uses its tuft to roast berries.

514.name: Simisear
514.description: A flame burns inside its body. It scatters embers from its head and tail to sear its opponents.

515.name: Panpour
515.description: It does not thrive in dry environments. It keeps itself damp by shooting water stored in its head tuft from its tail.

516.name: Simipour
516.description: The tuft on its head holds water. When the level runs low, it replenishes the tuft by siphoning up water with its tail.

517.name: Munna
517.description: Munna always float in the air. People whose dreams are eaten by them forget what the dreams had been about.

518.name: Musharna
518.description: The mist emanating from their foreheads is packed with the dreams of people and Pokémon.

519.name: Pidove
519.description: Each follows its Trainer’s orders as best it can, but they sometimes fail to understand complicated commands.

520.name: Tranquill
520.description: Many people believe that, deep in the forest where Tranquill live, there is a peaceful place where there is no war.

521.name: Unfezant
521.description: Males swing their head plumage to threaten opponents. The females’ flying abilities surpass those of the males.

522.name: Blitzle
522.description: Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use their flashing manes to communicate with one another.

523.name: Zebstrika
523.description: This ill-tempered Pokémon is dangerous because when it’s angry, it shoots lightning from its mane in all directions.

524.name: Roggenrola
524.description: They were discovered a hundred years ago in an earthquake fissure. Inside each one is an energy core.

525.name: Boldore
525.description: When it overflows with power, the orange crystal on its body glows. It looks for underground water in caves.

526.name: Gigalith
526.description: Compressing the energy from its internal core lets it fire off an attack capable of blowing away a mountain.

527.name: Woobat
527.description: Suction from its nostrils enables it to stick to cave walls during sleep. It leaves a heart-shaped mark behind.

528.name: Swoobat
528.description: Anyone who comes into contact with the ultrasonic waves emitted by a courting male experiences a positive mood shift.

529.name: Drilbur
529.description: It can dig through the ground at a speed of 30 mph. It could give a car running aboveground a good race.

530.name: Excadrill
530.description: More than 300 feet below the surface, they build mazelike nests. Their activity can be destructive to subway tunnels.

531.name: Audino
531.description: Its auditory sense is astounding. It has a radarlike ability to understand its surroundings through slight sounds.

531.name: Mega Audino
531.description: Its auditory sense is astounding. It has a radarlike ability to understand its surroundings through slight sounds.

532.name: Timburr
532.description: It fights by swinging a piece of lumber around. It is close to evolving when it can handle the lumber without difficulty.

533.name: Gurdurr
533.description: This Pokémon is so muscular and strongly built that even a group of wrestlers could not make it budge an inch.

534.name: Conkeldurr
534.description: They use concrete pillars as walking canes. They know moves that enable them to swing the pillars freely in battle.

535.name: Tympole
535.description: They warn others of danger by vibrating their cheeks to create a high-pitched sound.

536.name: Palpitoad
536.description: When they vibrate the bumps on their heads, they can make waves in water or earthquake-like vibrations on land.

537.name: Seismitoad
537.description: They shoot paralyzing liquid from their head bumps. They use vibration to hurt their opponents.

538.name: Throh
538.description: When they encounter foes bigger than themselves, they try to throw them. They always travel in packs of five.

539.name: Sawk
539.description: Tying their belts gets them pumped and makes their punches more destructive. Disturbing their training angers them.

540.name: Sewaddle
540.description: This Pokémon makes clothes for itself. It chews up leaves and sews them with sticky thread extruded from its mouth.

541.name: Swadloon
541.description: Forests where Swadloon live have superb foliage because the nutrients they make from fallen leaves nourish the plant life.

542.name: Leavanny
542.description: It keeps its eggs warm with heat from fermenting leaves. It also uses leaves to make warm wrappings for Sewaddle.

543.name: Venipede
543.description: It discovers what is going on around it by using the feelers on its head and tail. It is brutally aggressive.

544.name: Whirlipede
544.description: It is usually motionless, but when attacked, it rotates at high speed and then crashes into its opponent.

545.name: Scolipede
545.description: With quick movements, it chases down its foes, attacking relentlessly with its horns until it prevails.

546.name: Cottonee
546.description: They go wherever the wind takes them. On rainy days, their bodies are heavier, so they take shelter beneath big trees.

547.name: Whimsicott
547.description: Riding whirlwinds, they appear. These Pokémon sneak through gaps into houses and cause all sorts of mischief.

548.name: Petilil
548.description: Since they prefer moist, nutrient-rich soil, the areas where Petilil live are known to be good for growing plants.

549.name: Lilligant
549.description: Even veteran Trainers face a challenge in getting its beautiful flower to bloom. This Pokémon is popular with celebrities.

550.name: Basculin - Red-Striped Form
550.description: Red and blue Basculin usually do not get along, but sometimes members of one school mingle with the other’s school.

550.name: Basculin - Blue-Striped Form
550.description: Red and blue Basculin usually do not get along, but sometimes members of one school mingle with the other’s school.

551.name: Sandile
551.description: It moves along below the sand’s surface, except for its nose and eyes. A dark membrane shields its eyes from the sun.

552.name: Krokorok
552.description: The special membrane covering its eyes can sense the heat of objects, so it can see its surroundings even in darkness.

553.name: Krookodile
553.description: It can expand the focus of its eyes, enabling it to see objects in the far distance as if it were using binoculars.

554.name: Darumaka
554.description: When its internal fire is burning, it cannot calm down and it runs around. When the fire diminishes, it falls asleep.

555.name: Darmanitan
555.description: Its internal fire burns at 2,500° F, making enough power that it can destroy a dump truck with one punch.

555.name: Darmanitan - Zen Mode
555.description: Its internal fire burns at 2,500° F, making enough power that it can destroy a dump truck with one punch.

556.name: Maractus
556.description: It uses an up-tempo song and dance to drive away the bird Pokémon that prey on its flower seeds.

557.name: Dwebble
557.description: It makes a hole in a suitable rock. If that rock breaks, the Pokémon remains agitated until it locates a replacement.

558.name: Crustle
558.description: It possesses legs of enormous strength, enabling it to carry heavy slabs for many days, even when crossing arid land.

559.name: Scraggy
559.description: Its skin has a rubbery elasticity, so it can reduce damage by defensively pulling its skin up to its neck.

560.name: Scrafty
560.description: Groups of them beat up anything that enters their territory. Each can spit acidic liquid from its mouth.

561.name: Sigilyph
561.description: The guardians of an ancient city, they use their psychic power to attack enemies that invade their territory.

562.name: Yamask
562.description: These Pokémon arose from the spirits of people interred in graves in past ages. Each retains memories of its former life.

563.name: Cofagrigus
563.description: It has been said that they swallow those who get too close and turn them into mummies. They like to eat gold nuggets.

564.name: Tirtouga
564.description: About 100 million years ago, these Pokémon swam in oceans. It is thought they also went on land to attack prey.

565.name: Carracosta
565.description: They can live both in the ocean and on land. A slap from one of them is enough to open a hole in the bottom of a tanker.

566.name: Archen
566.description: Said to be an ancestor of bird Pokémon, they were unable to fly and moved about by hopping from one branch to another.

567.name: Archeops
567.description: They are intelligent and will cooperate to catch prey. From the ground, they use a running start to take flight.

568.name: Trubbish
568.description: The combination of garbage bags and industrial waste caused the chemical reaction that created this Pokémon.

569.name: Garbodor
569.description: It clenches opponents with its left arm and finishes them off with foul-smelling poison gas belched from its mouth.

570.name: Zorua
570.description: To protect themselves from danger, they hide their true identities by transforming into people and Pokémon.

571.name: Zoroark
571.description: Each has the ability to fool a large group of people simultaneously. They protect their lair with illusory scenery.

572.name: Minccino
572.description: They greet one another by rubbing each other with their tails, which are always kept well groomed and clean.

573.name: Cinccino
573.description: Their white fur feels amazing to touch. Their fur repels dust and prevents static electricity from building up.

574.name: Gothita
574.description: They intently observe both Trainers and Pokémon. Apparently, they are looking at something that only Gothita can see.

575.name: Gothorita
575.description: They use hypnosis to control people and Pokémon. Tales of Gothorita leading people astray are told in every corner.

576.name: Gothitelle
576.description: Starry skies thousands of light-years away are visible in the space distorted by their intense psychic power.

577.name: Solosis
577.description: Because their bodies are enveloped in a special liquid, they can survive in any environment.

578.name: Duosion
578.description: When their brains, now divided in two, are thinking the same thoughts, these Pokémon exhibit their maximum power.

579.name: Reuniclus
579.description: These remarkably intelligent Pokémon fight by controlling arms that can grip with rock-crushing power.

580.name: Ducklett
580.description: These bird Pokémon are excellent divers. They swim around in the water eating their favorite food--peat moss.

581.name: Swanna
581.description: It administers sharp, powerful pecks with its bill. It whips its long neck to deliver forceful repeated strikes.

582.name: Vanillite
582.description: The temperature of their breath is -58° F. They create snow crystals and make snow fall in the areas around them.

583.name: Vanillish
583.description: Snowy mountains are this Pokémon’s habitat. During an ancient ice age, they moved to southern areas.

584.name: Vanilluxe
584.description: Swallowing large amounts of water, they make snow clouds inside their bodies and attack their foes with violent blizzards.

585.name: Deerling - Spring Form
585.description: The color and scent of their fur changes to match the mountain grass. When they sense hostility, they hide in the grass.

585.name: Deerling - Summer Form
585.description: The color and scent of their fur changes to match the mountain grass. When they sense hostility, they hide in the grass.

585.name: Deerling - Autumn Form
585.description: The color and scent of their fur changes to match the mountain grass. When they sense hostility, they hide in the grass.

585.name: Deerling - Winter Form
585.description: The color and scent of their fur changes to match the mountain grass. When they sense hostility, they hide in the grass.

586.name: Sawsbuck - Spring Form
586.description: The plants growing on its horns change according to the season. The leaders of the herd possess magnificent horns.

586.name: Sawsbuck - Summer Form
586.description: The plants growing on its horns change according to the season. The leaders of the herd possess magnificent horns.

586.name: Sawsbuck - Autumn Form
586.description: The plants growing on its horns change according to the season. The leaders of the herd possess magnificent horns.

586.name: Sawsbuck - Winter Form
586.description: The plants growing on its horns change according to the season. The leaders of the herd possess magnificent horns.

587.name: Emolga
587.description: The energy made in its cheeks’ electric pouches is stored inside its membrane and released while it is gliding.

588.name: Karrablast
588.description: These mysterious Pokémon evolve when they receive electrical stimulation while they are in the same place as Shelmet.

589.name: Escavalier
589.description: They fly around at high speed, striking with their pointed spears. Even when in trouble, they face opponents bravely.

590.name: Foongus
590.description: It lures people in with its Poké Ball pattern, then releases poison spores. Why it resembles a Poké Ball is unknown.

591.name: Amoonguss
591.description: It lures prey close by dancing and waving its arm caps, which resemble Poké Balls, in a swaying motion.

592.name: Frillish
592.description: With its thin, veil-like arms wrapped around the body of its opponent, it sinks to the ocean floor.

593.name: Jellicent
593.description: They propel themselves by expelling absorbed seawater from their bodies. Their favorite food is life energy.

594.name: Alomomola
594.description: Floating in the open sea is how they live. When they find a wounded Pokémon, they embrace it and bring it to shore.

595.name: Joltik
595.description: Joltik that live in cities have learned a technique for sucking electricity from the outlets in houses.

596.name: Galvantula
596.description: They employ an electrically charged web to trap their prey. While it is immobilized by shock, they leisurely consume it.

597.name: Ferroseed
597.description: When threatened, it attacks by shooting a barrage of spikes, which gives it a chance to escape by rolling away.

598.name: Ferrothorn
598.description: It fights by swinging around its three spiky feelers. A hit from these steel spikes can reduce a boulder to rubble.

599.name: Klink
599.description: The two minigears that mesh together are predetermined. Each will rebound from other minigears without meshing.

600.name: Klang
600.description: By changing the direction in which it rotates, it communicates its feelings to others. When angry, it rotates faster.

601.name: Klinklang
601.description: Its red core functions as an energy tank. It fires the charged energy through its spikes into an area.

602.name: Tynamo
602.description: These Pokémon move in schools. They have an electricity-generating organ, so they discharge electricity if in danger.

603.name: Eelektrik
603.description: They coil around foes and shock them with electricity-generating organs that seem simply to be circular patterns.

604.name: Eelektross
604.description: They crawl out of the ocean using their arms. They will attack prey on shore and immediately drag it into the ocean.

605.name: Elgyem
605.description: It uses its strong psychic power to squeeze its opponent’s brain, causing unendurable headaches.

606.name: Beheeyem
606.description: It can manipulate an opponent’s memory. Apparently, it communicates by flashing its three different-colored fingers.

607.name: Litwick
607.description: Litwick shines a light that absorbs the life energy of people and Pokémon, which becomes the fuel that it burns.

608.name: Lampent
608.description: This ominous Pokémon is feared. Through cities it wanders, searching for the spirits of the fallen.

609.name: Chandelure
609.description: It absorbs a spirit, which it then burns. By waving the flames on its arms, it puts its foes into a hypnotic trance.

610.name: Axew
610.description: They mark their territory by leaving gashes in trees with their tusks. If a tusk breaks, a new one grows in quickly.

611.name: Fraxure
611.description: Since a broken tusk will not grow back, they diligently sharpen their tusks on river rocks after they’ve been fighting.

612.name: Haxorus
612.description: They are kind but can be relentless when defending territory. They challenge foes with tusks that can cut steel.

613.name: Cubchoo
613.description: Its nose is always running. It sniffs the snot back up because the mucus provides the raw material for its moves.

614.name: Beartic
614.description: It can make its breath freeze at will. Very able in the water, it swims around in northern seas and catches prey.

615.name: Cryogonal
615.description: When its body temperature goes up, it turns into steam and vanishes. When its temperature lowers, it returns to ice.

616.name: Shelmet
616.description: When attacked, it defends itself by closing the lid of its shell. It can spit a sticky, poisonous liquid.

617.name: Accelgor
617.description: When its body dries out, it weakens. So, to prevent dehydration, it wraps itself in many layers of thin membrane.

618.name: Stunfisk
618.description: Its skin is very hard, so it is unhurt even if stepped on by sumo wrestlers. It smiles when transmitting electricity.

619.name: Mienfoo
619.description: In fights, they dominate with onslaughts of flowing, continuous attacks. With their sharp claws, they cut enemies.

620.name: Mienshao
620.description: It wields the fur on its arms like a whip. Its arm attacks come with such rapidity that they cannot even be seen.

621.name: Druddigon
621.description: It warms its body by absorbing sunlight with its wings. When its body temperature falls, it can no longer move.

622.name: Golett
622.description: These Pokémon are thought to have been created by the science of an ancient and mysterious civilization.

623.name: Golurk
623.description: It flies across the sky at Mach speeds. Removing the seal on its chest makes its internal energy go out of control.

624.name: Pawniard
624.description: Blades comprise this Pokémon’s entire body. If battling dulls the blades, it sharpens them on stones by the river.

625.name: Bisharp
625.description: It leads a group of Pawniard. It battles to become the boss, but will be driven from the group if it loses.

626.name: Bouffalant
626.description: Their fluffy fur absorbs damage, even if they strike foes with a fierce headbutt.

627.name: Rufflet
627.description: They crush berries with their talons. They bravely stand up to any opponent, no matter how strong it is.

628.name: Braviary
628.description: They fight for their friends without any thought about danger to themselves. One can carry a car while flying.

629.name: Vullaby
629.description: Its wings are too tiny to allow it to fly. As the time approaches for it to evolve, it discards the bones it was wearing.

630.name: Mandibuzz
630.description: Watching from the sky, they swoop to strike weakened Pokémon on the ground. They decorate themselves with bones.

631.name: Heatmor
631.description: Using their very hot, flame-covered tongues, they burn through Durant’s steel bodies and consume their insides.

632.name: Durant
632.description: They attack in groups, covering themselves in steel armor to protect themselves from Heatmor.

633.name: Deino
633.description: They cannot see, so they tackle and bite to learn about their surroundings. Their bodies are covered in wounds.

634.name: Zweilous
634.description: After it has eaten up all the food in its territory, it moves to another area. Its two heads do not get along.

635.name: Hydreigon
635.description: This brutal Pokémon travels the skies on its six wings. Anything that moves seems like a foe to it, triggering its attack.

636.name: Larvesta
636.description: This Pokémon was believed to have been born from the sun. When it evolves, its entire body is engulfed in flames.

637.name: Volcarona
637.description: When volcanic ash darkened the atmosphere, it is said that Volcarona’s fire provided a replacement for the sun.

638.name: Cobalion
638.description: This legendary Pokémon battled against humans to protect Pokémon. Its personality is calm and composed.

639.name: Terrakion
639.description: This Pokémon came to the defense of Pokémon that had lost their homes in a war among humans.

640.name: Virizion
640.description: This Pokémon fought humans in order to protect its friends. Legends about it continue to be passed down.

641.name: Tornadus - Incarnate Forme
641.description: The lower half of its body is wrapped in a cloud of energy. It zooms through the sky at 200 mph.

641.name: Tornadus - Therian Forme
641.description: The lower half of its body is wrapped in a cloud of energy. It zooms through the sky at 200 mph.

642.name: Thundurus - Incarnate Forme
642.description: Countless charred remains mar the landscape of places through which Thundurus has passed.

642.name: Thundurus - Therian Forme
642.description: Countless charred remains mar the landscape of places through which Thundurus has passed.

643.name: Reshiram
643.description: This Pokémon appears in legends. It sends flames into the air from its tail, burning up everything around it.

644.name: Zekrom
644.description: Concealing itself in lightning clouds, it flies throughout the Unova region. It creates electricity in its tail.

645.name: Landorus - Incarnate Forme
645.description: Lands visited by Landorus grant such bountiful crops that it has been hailed as “The Guardian of the Fields.”

645.name: Landorus - Therian Forme
645.description: Lands visited by Landorus grant such bountiful crops that it has been hailed as “The Guardian of the Fields.”

646.name: Kyurem
646.description: It generates a powerful, freezing energy inside itself, but its body became frozen when the energy leaked out.

646.name: White Kyurem
646.description: It generates a powerful, freezing energy inside itself, but its body became frozen when the energy leaked out.

646.name: Black Kyurem
646.description: It generates a powerful, freezing energy inside itself, but its body became frozen when the energy leaked out.

647.name: Keldeo - Ordinary Form
647.description: By blasting water from its hooves, it can glide across water. It excels at using leg moves while battling.

647.name: Keldeo - Resolute Form
647.description: By blasting water from its hooves, it can glide across water. It excels at using leg moves while battling.

648.name: Meloetta - Aria Forme
648.description: Its melodies are sung with a special vocalization method that can control the feelings of those who hear it.

648.name: Meloetta - Pirouette Forme
648.description: Its melodies are sung with a special vocalization method that can control the feelings of those who hear it.

649.name: Genesect
649.description: Over 300 million years ago, it was feared as the strongest of hunters. It has been modified by Team Plasma.

650.name: Chespin
650.description: The quills on its head are usually soft. When it flexes them, the points become so hard and sharp that they can pierce rock.

651.name: Quilladin
651.description: It relies on its sturdy shell to deflect predators’ attacks. It counterattacks with its sharp quills.

652.name: Chesnaught
652.description: Its Tackle is forceful enough to flip a 50-ton tank. It shields its allies from danger with its own body.

653.name: Fennekin
653.description: Eating a twig fills it with energy, and its roomy ears give vent to air hotter than 390 degrees Fahrenheit.

654.name: Braixen
654.description: It has a twig stuck in its tail. With friction from its tail fur, it sets the twig on fire and launches into battle.

655.name: Delphox
655.description: It gazes into the flame at the tip of its branch to achieve a focused state, which allows it to see into the future.

656.name: Froakie
656.description: It secretes flexible bubbles from its chest and back. The bubbles reduce the damage it would otherwise take when attacked.

657.name: Frogadier
657.description: It can throw bubble-covered pebbles with precise control, hitting empty cans up to a hundred feet away.

658.name: Greninja
658.description: It creates throwing stars out of compressed water. When it spins them and throws them at high speed, these stars can split metal in two.

658.name: Ash-Greninja
658.description: It creates throwing stars out of compressed water. When it spins them and throws them at high speed, these stars can split metal in two.

659.name: Bunnelby
659.description: It has ears like shovels. Digging holes strengthens its ears so much that they can sever thick roots effortlessly.

660.name: Diggersby
660.description: With their powerful ears, they can heft boulders of a ton or more with ease. They can be a big help at construction sites.

661.name: Fletchling
661.description: These friendly Pokémon send signals to one another with beautiful chirps and tail-feather movements.

662.name: Fletchinder
662.description: From its beak, it expels embers that set the tall grass on fire. Then it pounces on the bewildered prey that pop out of the grass.

663.name: Talonflame
663.description: In the fever of an exciting battle, it showers embers from the gaps between its feathers and takes to the air.

664.name: Scatterbug
664.description: When under attack from bird Pokémon, it spews a poisonous black powder that causes paralysis on contact.

665.name: Spewpa
665.description: It lives hidden within thicket shadows. When predators attack, it quickly bristles the fur covering its body in an effort to threaten them.

666.name: Vivillon
666.description: Vivillon with many different patterns are found all over the world. These patterns are affected by the climate of their habitat.

667.name: Litleo
667.description: The stronger the opponent it faces, the more heat surges from its mane and the more power flows through its body.

668.name: Pyroar
668.description: With fiery breath of more than 10,000 degrees Fahrenheit, they viciously threaten any challenger. The females protect the pride’s cubs.

669.name: Flabébé
669.description: It draws out and controls the hidden power of flowers. The flower Flabébé holds is most likely part of its body.

670.name: Floette
670.description: It flutters around fields of flowers and cares for flowers that are starting to wilt. It draws out the hidden power of flowers to battle.

671.name: Florges
671.description: It claims exquisite flower gardens as its territory, and it obtains power from basking in the energy emitted by flowering plants.

672.name: Skiddo
672.description: Thought to be one of the first Pokémon to live in harmony with humans, it has a placid disposition.

673.name: Gogoat
673.description: It can tell how its Trainer is feeling by subtle shifts in the grip on its horns. This empathic sense lets them run as if one being.

674.name: Pancham
674.description: It does its best to be taken seriously by its enemies, but its glare is not sufficiently intimidating. Chewing on a leaf is its trademark.

675.name: Pangoro
675.description: Although it possesses a violent temperament, it won’t put up with bullying. It uses the leaf in its mouth to sense the movements of its enemies.

676.name: Furfrou
676.description: Trimming its fluffy fur not only makes it more elegant but also increases the swiftness of its movements.

677.name: Espurr
677.description: The organ that emits its intense psychic power is sheltered by its ears to keep power from leaking out.

678.name: Meowstic - Male
678.description: The eyeball patterns on the interior of its ears emit psychic energy. It keeps the patterns tightly covered because that power is too immense.

678.name: Meowstic - Female
678.description: The eyeball patterns on the interior of its ears emit psychic energy. It keeps the patterns tightly covered because that power is too immense.

679.name: Honedge
679.description: Apparently this Pokémon is born when a departed spirit inhabits a sword. It attaches itself to people and drinks their life force.

680.name: Doublade
680.description: When Honedge evolves, it divides into two swords, which cooperate via telepathy to coordinate attacks and slash their enemies to ribbons.

681.name: Aegislash
681.description: Generations of kings were attended by these Pokémon, which used their spectral power to manipulate and control people and Pokémon.

682.name: Spritzee
682.description: In the past, rather than using perfume, royal ladies carried a Spritzee that would waft a fragrance they liked.

683.name: Aromatisse
683.description: Its scent is so overpowering that, unless a Trainer happens to really enjoy the smell, he or she will have a hard time walking alongside it.

684.name: Swirlix
684.description: To entangle its opponents in battle, it extrudes white threads as sweet and sticky as cotton candy.

685.name: Slurpuff
685.description: Its sense of smell is 100 million times better than a human’s, so even the faintest scent tells it about everything in the area. It’s like it can see with its nose!

686.name: Inkay
686.description: Opponents who stare at the flashing of the light-emitting spots on its body become dazed and lose their will to fight.

687.name: Malamar
687.description: It lures its prey close with hypnotic motions, then wraps its tentacles around it before finishing it off with digestive fluids.

688.name: Binacle
688.description: They stretch and then contract, yanking their rocks along with them in bold hops. They eat seaweed that washes up on the shoreline.

689.name: Barbaracle
689.description: Barbaracle’s legs and hands have minds of their own, and they will move independently. But they usually follow the head’s orders.

690.name: Skrelp
690.description: Camouflaged as rotten kelp, they spray liquid poison on prey that approaches unawares and then finish it off.

691.name: Dragalge
691.description: Their poison is strong enough to eat through the hull of a tanker, and they spit it indiscriminately at anything that enters their territory.

692.name: Clauncher
692.description: Through controlled explosions of internal gas, it can expel water like a pistol shot. At close distances, it can shatter rock.

693.name: Clawitzer
693.description: By expelling water from the nozzle in the back of its claw, it can move at a speed of 60 knots.

694.name: Helioptile
694.description: They make their home in deserts. They can generate their energy from basking in the sun, so eating food is not a requirement.

695.name: Heliolisk
695.description: They flare their frills and generate energy. A single Heliolisk can generate sufficient electricity to power a skyscraper.

696.name: Tyrunt
696.description: This Pokémon was restored from a fossil. If something happens that it doesn’t like, it throws a tantrum and runs wild.

697.name: Tyrantrum
697.description: Thanks to its gargantuan jaws, which could shred thick metal plates as if they were paper, it was invincible in the ancient world it once inhabited.

698.name: Amaura
698.description: This ancient Pokémon was restored from part of its body that had been frozen in ice for over 100 million years.

699.name: Aurorus
699.description: The diamond-shaped crystals on its body expel air as cold as -240 degrees Fahrenheit, surrounding its enemies and encasing them in ice.

700.name: Sylveon
700.description: It wraps its ribbonlike feelers around the arm of its beloved Trainer and walks with him or her.

701.name: Hawlucha
701.description: Although its body is small, its proficient fighting skills enable it to keep up with big bruisers like Machamp and Hariyama.

702.name: Dedenne
702.description: It uses its tail to absorb electricity from power plants or from outlets in houses, and then it fires the electricity from its whiskers.

703.name: Carbink
703.description: It has slept underground for hundreds of millions of years since its birth. It’s occasionally found during the excavation of caves.

704.name: Goomy
704.description: The weakest Dragon-type Pokémon, it lives in damp, shady places, so its body doesn’t dry out.

705.name: Sliggoo
705.description: Its four horns are a high-performance radar system. It uses them to sense sounds and smells, rather than using ears or a nose.

706.name: Goodra
706.description: This very friendly Dragon-type Pokémon will hug its beloved Trainer, leaving that Trainer covered in sticky slime.

707.name: Klefki
707.description: These key collectors threaten any attackers by fiercely jingling their keys at them.

708.name: Phantump
708.description: These Pokémon are created when spirits possess rotten tree stumps. They prefer to live in abandoned forests.

709.name: Trevenant
709.description: Using its roots as a nervous system, it controls the trees in the forest. It’s kind to the Pokémon that reside in its body.

710.name: Pumpkaboo
710.description: The pumpkin body is inhabited by a spirit trapped in this world. As the sun sets, it becomes restless and active.

711.name: Gourgeist
711.description: Singing in eerie voices, they wander town streets on the night of the new moon. Anyone who hears their song is cursed.

712.name: Bergmite
712.description: Using air of -150 degrees Fahrenheit, they freeze opponents solid. They live in herds above the snow line on mountains.

713.name: Avalugg
713.description: Its ice-covered body is as hard as steel. Its cumbersome frame crushes anything that stands in its way.

714.name: Noibat
714.description: Even a robust wrestler will become dizzy and unable to stand when exposed to its 200,000-hertz ultrasonic waves.

715.name: Noivern
715.description: The ultrasonic waves it emits from its ears can reduce a large boulder to pebbles. It swoops out of the dark to attack.

716.name: Xerneas
716.description: Legends say it can share eternal life. It slept for a thousand years in the form of a tree before its revival.

717.name: Yveltal
717.description: When this legendary Pokémon’s wings and tail feathers spread wide and glow red, it absorbs the life force of living creatures.

719.name: Diancie
719.description: A sudden transformation of Carbink, its pink, glimmering body is said to be the loveliest sight in the whole world.

719.name: Mega Diancie
719.description: A sudden transformation of Carbink, its pink, glimmering body is said to be the loveliest sight in the whole world.

720.name: Hoopa Confined
720.description: This troublemaker sends anything and everything to faraway places using its loop, which can warp space.

720.name: Hoopa Unbound
720.description: This troublemaker sends anything and everything to faraway places using its loop, which can warp space.

721.name: Volcanion
721.description: It lets out billows of steam and disappears into the dense fog. It’s said to live in mountains where humans do not tread.

722.name: Rowlet
722.description: Silently it glides, drawing near its targets. Before they even notice it, it begins to pelt them with vicious kicks.

723.name: Dartrix
723.description: A bit of a dandy, it spends its free time preening its wings. Its preoccupation with any dirt on its plumage can leave it unable to battle.

724.name: Decidueye
724.description: It fires arrow quills from its wings with such precision, they can pierce a pebble at distances over a hundred yards.

725.name: Litten
725.description: While grooming itself, it builds up fur inside its stomach. It sets the fur alight and spews fiery attacks, which change based on how it coughs.

726.name: Torracat
726.description: It can act spoiled if it grows close to its Trainer. A powerful Pokémon, its sharp claws can leave its Trainer’s whole body covered in scratches.

727.name: Incineroar
727.description: This Pokémon has a violent, selfish disposition. If it’s not in the mood to listen, it will ignore its Trainer’s orders with complete nonchalance.

728.name: Popplio
728.description: This Pokémon snorts body fluids from its nose, blowing balloons to smash into its foes. It’s famous for being a hard worker.

729.name: Brionne
729.description: It cares deeply for its companions. When its Trainer is feeling down, it performs a cheery dance to try and help.

730.name: Primarina
730.description: It controls its water balloons with song. The melody is learned from others of its kind and is passed down from one generation to the next.

731.name: Pikipek
731.description: This Pokémon feeds on berries, whose leftover seeds become the ammunition for the attacks it fires off from its mouth.

732.name: Trumbeak
732.description: It eats berries and stores their seeds in its beak. When it encounters enemies or prey, it fires off all the seeds in a burst.

733.name: Toucannon
733.description: When it battles, its beak heats up. The temperature can easily exceed 212 degrees Fahrenheit, causing severe burns when it hits.

734.name: Yungoos
734.description: It wanders around in a never-ending search for food. At dusk, it collapses from exhaustion and falls asleep on the spot.

735.name: Gumshoos
735.description: When it finds a trace of its prey, it patiently stakes out the location...but it’s always snoozing by nightfall.

736.name: Grubbin
736.description: They often gather near places frequented by electric Pokémon in order to avoid being attacked by bird Pokémon.

737.name: Charjabug
737.description: Its body is capable of storing electricity. On camping trips, people are grateful to have one around.

738.name: Vikavolt
738.description: It zips around, on sharp lookout for an opening. It concentrates electrical energy within its large jaws and uses it to zap its enemies.

739.name: Crabrawler
739.description: While guarding its weak points with its pincers, it looks for an opening and unleashes punches. When it loses, it foams at the mouth and faints.

740.name: Crabominable
740.description: It aimed for the top but got lost and ended up on a snowy mountain. Being forced to endure the cold, this Pokémon evolved and grew fur.

742.name: Cutiefly
742.description: It feeds on the nectar and pollen of flowers. Because it’s able to sense auras, it can identify which flowers are about to bloom.

743.name: Ribombee
743.description: It rolls up pollen into puffs. It makes many different varieties, some used as food and others used in battle.

744.name: Rockruff
744.description: This Pokémon has lived with people since times long ago. It can sense when its Trainer is in the dumps and will stick close by its Trainer’s side.

747.name: Mareanie
747.description: It plunges the poison spike on its head into its prey. When the prey has weakened, Mareanie deals the finishing blow with its 10 tentacles.

748.name: Toxapex
748.description: Those attacked by Toxapex’s poison will suffer intense pain for three days and three nights. Post-recovery, there will be some aftereffects.

749.name: Mudbray
749.description: It has a stubborn, individualistic disposition. Eating dirt, making mud, and playing in the mire all form part of its daily routine.

750.name: Mudsdale
750.description: Its heavy, mud-covered kicks are its best means of attack, and it can reduce large trucks to scrap without breaking a sweat.

751.name: Dewpider
751.description: When two Dewpider meet, they display their water bubbles to each other. Then the one with the smaller bubble gets out of the other’s way.

752.name: Araquanid
752.description: Despite what its appearance suggests, it cares for others. If it finds vulnerable, weak Pokémon, it protectively brings them into its water bubble.

753.name: Fomantis
753.description: When the sun rises, Fomantis spreads its four leaves and bathes in the sunlight. The tip of its head has a pleasant aroma.

754.name: Lurantis
754.description: It requires a lot of effort to maintain Lurantis’s vivid coloring, but some collectors enjoy this work and treat it as their hobby.

755.name: Morelull
755.description: As it drowses the day away, it nourishes itself by sucking from tree roots. It wakens at the fall of night, wandering off in search of a new tree.

756.name: Shiinotic
756.description: Forests where Shiinotic live are treacherous to enter at night. People confused by its strange lights can never find their way home again.

757.name: Salandit
757.description: Volcanoes or dry, craggy places are its home. It emanates a sweet-smelling poisonous gas that attracts bug Pokémon, then attacks them.

758.name: Salazzle
758.description: For some reason, only females have been found. It creates a reverse harem of male Salandit that it lives with.

759.name: Stufful
759.description: Despite its adorable appearance, when it gets angry and flails about, its arms and legs could knock a pro wrestler sprawling.

760.name: Bewear
760.description: This Pokémon has the habit of hugging its companions. Many Trainers have left this world after their spines were squashed by its hug.

761.name: Bounsweet
761.description: Although it’s too sugary for human consumption, Bounsweet’s sweat can be watered down into a juice with just the right amount of sweetness.

762.name: Steenee
762.description: The sepals on its head developed to protect its body. These are quite hard, so even if pecked by bird Pokémon, this Pokémon is totally fine.

763.name: Tsareena
763.description: Its long, striking legs aren’t just for show but to be used to kick with skill. In victory, it shows off by kicking the defeated, laughing boisterously.

764.name: Comfey
764.description: It stretches sticky vines out from its head and picks flowers to adorn itself with. When it doesn’t have any flowers, it feels uneasy.

765.name: Oranguru
765.description: Known for its extreme intelligence, this Pokémon will look down on inexperienced Trainers, so it’s best suited to veteran Trainers.

766.name: Passimian
766.description: They battle with hard berries for weapons. Their techniques are passed from the boss to the group, generation upon generation.

767.name: Wimpod
767.description: Its habitat varies from beaches to seabeds. A natural scavenger, it will gleefully chow down on anything edible, no matter how rotten.

768.name: Golisopod
768.description: It battles skillfully with its six arms, but spends most of its time peacefully meditating in caves deep beneath the sea.

769.name: Sandygast
769.description: It takes control of anyone who puts a hand in its mouth. And so it adds to the accumulation of its sand-mound body.

770.name: Palossand
770.description: Possessed people controlled by this Pokémon transformed its sand mound into a castle. As it evolved, its power to curse grew ever stronger.

771.name: Pyukumuku
771.description: It lives in shallow seas, such as areas near a beach. It can eject its internal organs, which it uses to engulf its prey or battle enemies.

772.name: Type: Null
772.description: The heavy control mask it wears suppresses its intrinsic capabilities. This Pokémon has some hidden special power.

773.name: Silvally
773.description: Its trust in its partner is what awakens it. This Pokémon is capable of changing its type, a flexibility that is well displayed in battle.

775.name: Komala
775.description: It is born asleep, and it dies asleep. All its movements are apparently no more than the results of it tossing and turning in its dreams.

776.name: Turtonator
776.description: The shell on its back is chemically unstable and explodes violently if struck. The hole in its stomach is its weak point.

777.name: Togedemaru
777.description: The spiny fur on its back is normally at rest. When this Pokémon becomes agitated, its fur stands on end and stabs into its attackers.

778.name: Mimikyu - Disguised Form
778.description: Its actual appearance is unknown. A scholar who saw what was under its rag was overwhelmed by terror and died from the shock.

778.name: Mimikyu - Busted Form
778.description: Its actual appearance is unknown. A scholar who saw what was under its rag was overwhelmed by terror and died from the shock.

779.name: Bruxish
779.description: When it unleashes its psychic power from the protuberance on its head, the grating sound of grinding teeth echoes through the area.

780.name: Drampa
780.description: This Pokémon is friendly to people and loves children most of all. It comes from deep in the mountains to play with children it likes in town.

781.name: Dhelmise
781.description: The soul of seaweed adrift in the waves became reborn as this Pokémon. It maintains itself with new infusions of seabed detritus and seaweed.

782.name: Jangmo-o
782.description: It expresses its feelings by smacking its scales. Metallic sounds echo through the tall mountains where Jangmo-o lives.

783.name: Hakamo-o
783.description: It sheds and regrows its scales on a continuous basis. The scales become harder and sharper each time they’re regrown.

784.name: Kommo-o
784.description: Its rigid scales function as offense and defense. In the past, its scales were processed and used to make weapons and other commodities.

785.name: Tapu Koko
785.description: It confuses its enemies by flying too quickly for the eye to follow. It has a hair-trigger temper but forgets what made it angry an instant later.

786.name: Tapu Lele
786.description: As it flutters about, it scatters its strangely glowing scales. Touching them is said to restore good health on the spot.

787.name: Tapu Bulu
787.description: The guardian deity of Ula’ula is a lazy Pokémon. It commands plants to immobilize its foes and then deals them a savage blow with its horns.

788.name: Tapu Fini
788.description: The dense fog it creates brings the downfall and destruction of its confused enemies. Ocean currents are the source of its energy.

789.name: Cosmog
789.description: In ages past, it was called the child of the stars. It’s said to be a Pokémon from another world, but no specific details are known.

790.name: Cosmoem
790.description: There’s something accumulating around the black core within its hard shell. People think this Pokémon may come from another world.

791.name: Solgaleo
791.description: It is said to live in another world. The intense light it radiates from the surface of its body can make the darkest of nights light up like midday.

791.name: Solgaleo - Radiant Sun
791.description: It is said to live in another world. The intense light it radiates from the surface of its body can make the darkest of nights light up like midday.

792.name: Lunala
792.description: Said to live in another world, this Pokémon devours light, drawing the moonless dark veil of night over the brightness of day.

792.name: Lunala - Full Moon
792.description: Said to live in another world, this Pokémon devours light, drawing the moonless dark veil of night over the brightness of day.

793.name: Nihilego
793.description: One of the Ultra Beasts. It’s unclear whether or not this Pokémon is sentient, but sometimes it can be observed behaving like a young girl.

794.name: Buzzwole
794.description: This Ultra Beast appeared from another world. It shows off its body, but whether that display is a boast or a threat remains unclear.

795.name: Pheromosa
795.description: One of the Ultra Beasts. It refuses to touch anything, perhaps because it senses some uncleanness in this world.

796.name: Xurkitree
796.description: One of the mysterious life-forms known as Ultra Beasts. Astonishing electric shocks emanate from its entire body, according to witnesses.

797.name: Celesteela
797.description: One kind of Ultra Beast. Witnesses have seen it burn down a forest by expelling gas from its two arms.

798.name: Kartana
798.description: This Ultra Beast came from the Ultra Wormhole. It seems not to attack enemies on its own, but its sharp body is a dangerous weapon in itself.

799.name: Guzzlord
799.description: A dangerous Ultra Beast, it appears to be eating constantly, but for some reason its droppings have never been found.

801.name: Magearna
801.description: This artificial Pokémon, constructed more than 500 years ago, can understand human speech but cannot itself speak.

802.name: Marshadow
802.description: It slips into the shadows of others and mimics their powers and movements. As it improves, it becomes stronger than those it’s imitating.

803.name: Poipole
803.description: An Ultra Beast that lives in a different world, it cackles wildly as it sprays its opponents with poison from the needles on its head.

804.name: Naganadel
804.description: One kind of Ultra Beast, it fires a glowing, venomous liquid from its needles. This liquid is also immensely adhesive.

805.name: Stakataka
805.description: When stone walls started moving and attacking, the brute’s true identity was this mysterious life-form, which brings to mind an Ultra Beast.

806.name: Blacephalon
806.description: A UB that appeared from an Ultra Wormhole, it causes explosions, then takes advantage of opponents’ surprise to rob them of their vitality.

807.name: Zeraora
807.description: It electrifies its claws and tears its opponents apart with them. Even if they dodge its attack, they’ll be electrocuted by the flying sparks.
